#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.80"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.80:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:0.2"
msgid "8. Khajjanīyavagga "
msgstr "8. Itchy "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.80:0.3"
msgid "80. Piṇḍolyasutta "
msgstr "80. Beggars "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.80:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā kismiñcideva pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇāmetvā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kapilavatthuṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, having dismissed the mendicant Saṅgha for some reason, robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Kapilavatthu for alms. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:1.3"
msgid "Kapilavatthusmiṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena mahāvanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya. "
msgstr "He wandered for alms in Kapilavatthu. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Great Wood, "

msgctxt "sn22.80:1.4"
msgid "Mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā beluvalaṭṭhikāya mūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "plunged deep into it, and sat at the root of a young wood apple tree for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.80:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.2"
msgid "“mayā kho bhikkhusaṅgho pabāḷho. "
msgstr "“I’ve sent the mendicant Saṅgha away. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.3"
msgid "Santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ. "
msgstr "But there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ mamaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr "Not seeing me they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma vacchassa taruṇassa mātaraṃ apassantassa siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo; "
msgstr "If a young calf doesn’t see its mother it may change and fall apart. … "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.6"
msgid "evameva santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ tesaṃ mamaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma bījānaṃ taruṇānaṃ udakaṃ alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo; "
msgstr "Or if young seedlings don’t get water they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.8"
msgid "evameva santettha … pe … "
msgstr "In the same way, there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.9"
msgid "tesaṃ mamaṃ alabhantānaṃ dassanāya siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr "Not seeing me they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:2.10"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yatheva mayā pubbe bhikkhusaṅgho anuggahito, evameva etarahi anuggaṇheyyaṃ bhikkhusaṅghan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I support the mendicant Saṅgha now as I did in the past?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.92, sc3
#. VAR: samiñjitaṃ → sammiñjitaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.80:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito bhagavato purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati knew what the Buddha was thinking. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said: "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.3"
msgid "“evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One! "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.4"
msgid "Bhagavatā, bhante, bhikkhusaṃgho pabāḷho. "
msgstr "The Buddha has sent the mendicant Saṅgha away. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.5"
msgid "Santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ. "
msgstr "But there are mendicants who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. … "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.6"
msgid "Tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma vacchassa taruṇassa mātaraṃ apassantassa siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.8"
msgid "evameva santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma bījānaṃ taruṇānaṃ udakaṃ alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.10"
msgid "evameva santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ alabhantānaṃ dassanāya siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.11"
msgid "Abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ; "
msgstr "May the Buddha be happy with the mendicant Saṅgha! "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.12"
msgid "abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ. "
msgstr "May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha! "

msgctxt "sn22.80:3.13"
msgid "Yatheva bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito, evameva etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghan”ti. "
msgstr "May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.80:4.1"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:4.2"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing that the Buddha had consented, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.93, sc5
msgctxt "sn22.80:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena nigrodhārāmo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the Banyan Tree Monastery, where he sat on the seat spread out. "

#. VAR: abhisaṅkhāsi → abhisaṅkhāresi (s1-3, km) | abhisaṅkhāyi (pts1) | abhisaṅkharoti (mr)
#. VAR: ekadvīhikāya sārajjamānarūpā yenāhaṃ → etthantare pāṭho syā1-3, kaṃ potthakesu
#. VAR: yena bhagavā (bj)
msgctxt "sn22.80:5.2"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi yathā te bhikkhū ekadvīhikāya sārajjamānarūpā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkameyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Then he used his psychic power to will that the mendicants would come to him timidly, alone or in pairs. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:5.3"
msgid "Tepi bhikkhū ekadvīhikāya sārajjamānarūpā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Those mendicants approached the Buddha timidly, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them: "

# NOTE: Not sure about BB’s “lowest” for anta here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.80:6.1"
msgid "“Antamidaṃ, bhikkhave, jīvikānaṃ yadidaṃ piṇḍolyaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, this relying on alms is an extreme way to live. "

# NOTE: I found BB’s note here confusing. For the record, kapāla is not found in the text, but in the commentary.
msgctxt "sn22.80:6.2"
msgid "Abhisāpoyaṃ, bhikkhave, lokasmiṃ piṇḍolo vicarasi pattapāṇīti. "
msgstr "The world curses you: ‘You beggar, walking bowl in hand!’ "

# NOTE: The meaning of atthavasika is clarified at https://suttacentral.net/pi/pi-tv-pvr14. A mendicant who is approaching the sangha with some litigation should do so, maong a long list of reasons: atthavasikena bhavitabbaṃ no parisa­kap­pi­kena. To paraphrase, this seems to mean “looking for a genuinely good outcome for all concerned, not trying to get excused by the assembly”. I choose “earnest” as an English term with a similar sense.
msgctxt "sn22.80:6.3"
msgid "Tañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, kulaputtā upenti atthavasikā, atthavasaṃ paṭicca; "
msgstr "Yet earnest and gentlemen take it up for a good reason. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:6.4"
msgid "neva rājābhinītā, na corābhinītā, na iṇaṭṭā, na bhayaṭṭā, na ājīvikāpakatā; "
msgstr "Not because they’ve been forced to by kings or bandits, or because they’re in debt or threatened, or to earn a living. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:6.5"
msgid "api ca kho otiṇṇāmha jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi dukkhotiṇṇā dukkhaparetā "
msgstr "But because they’re swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. They’re swamped by suffering, mired in suffering. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:6.6"
msgid "appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethāti. "
msgstr "And they think, ‘Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.80:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ pabbajito cāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kulaputto. "
msgstr "That’s how this gentleman has gone forth. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:7.2"
msgid "So ca hoti abhijjhālu kāmesu tibbasārāgo byāpannacitto paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo muṭṭhassati asampajāno asamāhito vibbhantacitto pākatindriyo. "
msgstr "Yet they covet sensual pleasures; they’re infatuated, full of ill will and hateful intent. They are unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with straying mind and undisciplined faculties. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:7.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, chavālātaṃ ubhatopadittaṃ majjhe gūthagataṃ, neva gāme kaṭṭhatthaṃ pharati, nāraññe kaṭṭhatthaṃ pharati. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a firebrand for lighting a funeral pyre, burning at both ends, and smeared with dung in the middle. It couldn’t be used as timber either in the village or the wilderness. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:7.4"
msgid "Tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi gihibhogā ca parihīno, sāmaññatthañca na paripūreti. "
msgstr "I say that person is just like this. They’ve missed out on the pleasures of the lay life, and haven’t fulfilled the goal of the ascetic life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn22.80:8.1"
msgid "Tayome, bhikkhave, akusalavitakkā—"
msgstr "There are these three unskillful thoughts. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:8.2"
msgid "kāmavitakko, byāpādavitakko, vihiṃsāvitakko. "
msgstr "Sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:8.3"
msgid "Ime ca bhikkhave, tayo akusalavitakkā kva aparisesā nirujjhanti? "
msgstr "And where do these three unskillful thoughts cease without anything left over? "

msgctxt "sn22.80:8.4"
msgid "Catūsu vā satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittassa viharato animittaṃ vā samādhiṃ bhāvayato. "
msgstr "In those who meditate with their mind firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation; or who develop signless immersion. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:8.5"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva animitto samādhi bhāvetuṃ. "
msgstr "Just this much is quite enough motivation to develop signless immersion. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:8.6"
msgid "Animitto, bhikkhave, samādhi bhāvito bahulīkato mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso. "
msgstr "When signless immersion is developed and cultivated it is very fruitful and beneficial. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.94, sc9
msgctxt "sn22.80:9.1"
msgid "Dvemā, bhikkhave, diṭṭhiyo—"
msgstr "There are these two views. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.2"
msgid "bhavadiṭṭhi ca vibhavadiṭṭhi ca. "
msgstr "Views favoring continued existence and views favoring ending existence. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.3"
msgid "Tatra kho, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "A noble disciple reflects on this: "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.4"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho taṃ kiñci lokasmiṃ yamahaṃ upādiyamāno na vajjavā assan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Is there anything in the world that I could grasp without fault?’ "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.5"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.6"
msgid "‘natthi nu kho taṃ kiñci lokasmiṃ yamahaṃ upādiyamāno na vajjavā assaṃ. "
msgstr "‘There’s nothing in the world that I could grasp without fault. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.7"
msgid "Ahañhi rūpaññeva upādiyamāno upādiyeyyaṃ vedanaññeva … "
msgstr "For in grasping I would grasp only at form, feeling, "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.8"
msgid "saññaññeva … "
msgstr "perception, "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.9"
msgid "saṅkhāreyeva viññāṇaññeva upādiyamāno upādiyeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "choices, or consciousness. "

#. VAR: assa → ayaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.80:9.10"
msgid "Tassa me assa upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "That grasping of mine would be a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.11"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.12"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhaveyyuṃ. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition that gives rise to old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. "

msgctxt "sn22.80:9.13"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo assā’ti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.80:10.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn22.80:10.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.9"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.80:10.10"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.80:10.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.80:10.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.13"
msgid "tasmātiha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "“So you should truly see … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.14"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … "
msgstr "Seeing this … "

msgctxt "sn22.80:10.15"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.80:10.16"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

